## Versions

Python: 3.11
NLTK: 3.9.1
matplotlib: 3.9.2
numpy: 1.26.4
scipy: 1.14.1

## Runtime
Run on i9-13900HX CPU.
Train and plot the accuracy-train data size cost 66.53s. (Size increment = 500 from 500 to 14500)
Train and plot the accuracy-train data size cost 33.07s. (Size increment = 1000 from 500 to 14500)
Plot the speed vs length curve cost 14.57s.

## Additional Features
I realize plotting a learning curve for the tagger (accuracy as a function of training data size) and
plotting a speed vs. sentence length curve. The code is in the corpus_handler.py file and marked with '# Extra'.